From: gint project
Subject: [PATCH] AMDGPU s_setpc_b64 O(1) jump-table dispatch for interpreter kernels

Enables LLVM 22.1's AMDGPU backend to lower a dense dispatch `switch` (marked
with `!amdgpu.skip.lowerswitch` metadata) into an O(1) `s_setpc_b64` jump
table instead of an O(log N) comparison/bit-test tree. Targeted at bytecode-
interpreter kernels (e.g. gint) that dispatch one program per wave, where the
dispatch index is uniform across the wave.

Three parts:

1. LowerSwitch skip — a switch carrying `!amdgpu.skip.lowerswitch` is left
   intact (preserved into ISel) instead of being converted to a binary
   search tree.   [lib/Transforms/Utils/LowerSwitch.cpp]

2. StructurizeCFG skip — regions whose terminator is a switch with the skip
   metadata are bypassed (StructurizeCFG requires BranchInst terminators and
   would otherwise crash/restructure). UnifyLoopExits likewise bypasses them.
   [lib/Transforms/Scalar/StructurizeCFG.cpp, lib/Transforms/Utils/UnifyLoopExits.cpp]

3. AMDGPU BR_JT lowering + s_setpc dispatch:
   - BlockAddress materialization via the existing PC-relative reloc infra
     (s_getpc + s_add with rel32).   [SIISelLowering.{h,cpp}]
   - LowerBR_JT produces the SI_BR_JT pseudo; MCInstLower handles
     MO_BlockAddress / MO_JumpTableIndex.   [SIISelLowering.{h,cpp},
     AMDGPUMCInstLower.cpp, SIInstrInfo.{td,cpp}, SIInstructions.td]
   - SIExpandJTDispatch (new pre-RA pass) expands SI_BR_JT into
     s_getpc -> s_add (JTI-PostGetPC, split &0xFFFFFFFF/>>32) -> s_load ->
     sext -> s_add/s_addc -> s_setpc. A MO_JumpTableIndex operand is kept on
     s_getpc so BranchFolding's jump-table liveness scan keeps the table.
     [SIExpandJTDispatch.cpp, AMDGPU.h, CMakeLists.txt, AMDGPUTargetMachine.cpp]
   - Jump tables forced into .text (same section as code) so EK_LabelDifference32
     entries and the &0xFFFFFFFF/>>32 offset split are same-section label
     differences that the assembler resolves.   [AMDGPUTargetObjectFile.{h,cpp}]

Verified on gfx1201 (RDNA3.5) with the gint interpreter (106-opcode dispatch):
full test suite passes, dispatch is genuine s_setpc_b64 (138 dispatch sites,
17 jump tables), and the interpreter's GPU kernel time drops below torch eager.

Build: standard cmake+ninja LLVM build with -DLLVM_TARGETS_TO_BUILD=AMDGPU.
Apply:  patch -p1 < amdgpu-jt-dispatch.patch
        (from the llvm-project source root, against the 22.1.0 release tree)

---
